{{Infobox football biography |name = Philippe Sandler |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|2|10|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Amsterdam]], Netherlands |height = {{height|m=1.88}}<ref name = "SW"/> |position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]] |currentclub = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |clubnumber = 34 |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] |years1 = 2016–2018 |clubs1 = [[PEC Zwolle]] |caps1 = 30 |goals1 = 0 |years2 = 2018– |clubs2 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |caps2 = 0 |goals2 = 0 |nationalyears1 = |nationalteam1 = [[Netherlands national under-20 football team|Netherlands U20]] |nationalcaps1 = |nationalgoals1 = |club-update = 19:55, 6 January 2019 (UTC) }} '''Philippe Sandler''' (born 10 February 1997) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for English club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre back]].
==Club career== Born in [[Amsterdam]], Sandler began his senior career with [[PEC Zwolle]] in the 2016–17 season,<ref name = "SW"/> having previously played youth football for [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]].<ref name = "VI">{{cite web|url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/sandler-met-halfjaar-vertraging-speler-van-manchester-city|title=Sandler met halfjaar vertraging speler van Manchester City|date=31 January 2018|accessdate=22 August 2018|language=Dutch|publisher=Voetbal International}}</ref>
In January 2018 it was announced that Sandler would leave PEC Zwolle to join English club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the summer of 2018, for a transfer fee reported to be between €2.5 and 3 million.<ref name = "VI"/> The transfer went through on 31 July 2018.<ref name = "BBC">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45025425|title=Philippe Sandler: Manchester City sign Dutch defender from PEC Zwolle|date=31 July 2018|accessdate=1 August 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> Sandler requested the number 34 shirt in tribute to former Ajax teammate [[Abdelhak Nouri]], who collapsed and suffered brain damage, ending his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/bbcthree/article/abbf8564-5453-4f69-9a08-5d85630a5268|title=The touching reason players are wearing the number 34|date=8 January 2019|accessdate=9 January 2019|author=Ciaran Varley|publisher=BBC}}</ref>
Sandler made his City debut on 6 January 2019, coming on as a substitute in a 7-0 win over [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] in the [[FA Cup]].<ref name = "2018-19"/>
==International career== Sandler has represented the Netherlands at [[Netherlands national under-20 football team|under-20]] level.<ref name = "BBC"/>
